Package org.mapfish.print.attribute

Contains the attribute type and implementations.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Attribute
    Represents an attribute passed in from a web-client to be used to populate the report.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ArrayReflectiveAttribute<Value>
    An attribute which is essentially a ReflectiveAttribute but rather than representing a single object it represents an array of objects.
    FeaturesAttribute
    Attribute for GeoJson features collection.
    FeaturesAttribute.FeaturesAttributeValues
    The value of FeaturesAttribute.
    FloatAttribute
    A float type attribute.
    HttpRequestHeadersAttribute
    Attribute representing the headers from the request.
    HttpRequestHeadersAttribute.Value
    The object containing the attribute data.
    IntegerAttribute
    An integer type attribute.
    LegendAttribute
    Objects needed by the LegendProcessor.
    LegendAttribute.LegendAttributeValue
    The data required to render a map legend.
    NorthArrowAttribute
    The attributes for CreateNorthArrowProcessor.
    PrimitiveAttribute<Value>
    A type of attribute whose value is a primitive type.
    ReflectiveAttribute<Value>
    Used for attribute that can have defaults specified in the YAML config file.
    ScalebarAttribute
    The attributes for CreateScalebarProcessor.
    StringAttribute
    Attribute that reads a string from the request data.
    StyleAttribute
    Attribute for GeoJson Styles collection.
    StyleAttribute.StylesAttributeValues
    The value of StyleAttribute.
    TableAttribute
    The attributes for TableProcessor.
    TableAttribute.TableAttributeValue
    The value of TableAttribute.
    TableListAttribute
    The attributes for TableListProcessor.
    TableListAttribute.TableListAttributeValue
    The value of TableAttribute.
  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    InternalAttribute
    An annotation indicating that the attribute should not be printed in client config (client does not need to know about it) because it is registered automatically.
